{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_pakula_ver02/data/sn84026749/00222254383/1927011701/0315.xml":{"full_text":"Splinter Curbed Speech\n\"DRITJSH surgeons, by removing a splinter from his finger,\nrecently restored to an amateur boxer the powers of speech\nand hearing, which he had lost two years before when struck on\nthe neck in a boxing match.\nGOLDEN ROADS\nA Soul-Stirring Story of Jubilant Love and Bitter Remorse\nof a Typist and Telephone Operator, by a Well-\nKnown Author\nRead This First:\nGay Moore and l\u00aber cousin, Christine Noe. are employed in the Wall\nstreet house of Johnstone Baird, Gay as a typist, and Christine as\ntelephone operator. Christine is in love with Roger Pennington, called\nPenny by his intimates, whose wealth and social position appeal to\nher love of luxury. Stanley Baird is in love with Gay. Gay returns\nhis love, but knowing of the friendship existing between Johnstone\nB r d a woman known as the \"Lilac Lady,\u201d feat\u2019s that Stanley\ninherit his father\u2019s vices and grows doubtful of his love for her.\nChristine encourages the attentions of Ivor Barclay to arouse Penny's\njealousy. She goes to a road house of doubtful reputation with Bar\nclay, but Gay. overhearing the plan, enlists the aid of Stanley and\nrter Christine. Christine, humiliated, is taken home. Gay,\nwhile looking for Christine, inadvertently. opens the door of a private\nroom in the road house and discovers Johnstone Baird and the \"Lilac\nl ady\u201d dining alone. .She fears that Mr. Baird will misunderstand her\nown presence sit questionable a resort, and wonders what the\nconsequences will be to Stanley and herself. Gay receives a note\nfrom Stanley\u2019s mother inviting her to tea. She goes and the tea ends\nin .a scene between Johnstone Baird and Gay, in which he accuses\nher of marrying Stan for his money. Gay tells hint she wouldn\u2019t\nmarry Stan. However, Stan convinces Iter of his love, leaves home\nand takes a position as automobile mechanic. She hears nothing from\nhim until Christmas. Suddeny Penny tells Gay that Stan is ill. She\ngoes to linn in the hospital. Stan\u2019s family raise a row and disown\nhim when they discover he has been working in such an humble posi\ntion. However, Gay and Stan make plans for their wedding, which\ntakes place in February, and after a, short honeymoon, they return to\nthe city, as Stan wants to get back to work as quickly us possible.\nGay and Stan start housekeeping in a tiny,\" walk-up apartment,\nlurnished partly on the instalment plan and partly with furniture\nthat Jaimie and Mary give them. Meanwhile Christine fails to\nunderstand the ambition that is driving to make good in his\nposition, and jealously lays, the blame on Peggy Baird.\nChristiue, infuriated by Penny\u2019s seeming neglect, tells him she is\nto Stacia\u2019s. He accuses her of a rendezvous with Ivor Barclay.\nLhristme goes to Stacia's and Penny comes after her in an intoxicated\ncondition. Stacia goes to a party and leaves them alone, coming in at\nbreak to find them sitting jn a corner of the davenport fast asleep.\nGay and Stan are blissfully liappytin their apartment. Stan tells\nGay he and his \"boss\u201d are working on an invention: he brings works\nhome to do nights. Gay watches him delightedly. They prepare to\nf&y 6 .V ,e,r dinner party, with Christine and Penny as guests.\nChristine arrives at the apartment and tells Gay she is a fool\nfor living so when she might have every luxury.\nNow Go On With The Story.\nCl AY sprang to the. telephone,\nJ laughing. \"Gee, that\u2019s luck!\nSupposing I hadn\u2019t it! Supposing\u2014\nwell, if Christy will help now\u2014\u201d\nCHAPTER 29\nGay arranged for her cousin to\ncome up to the flat. She was to\n\u25a0top on the way and buy the shirt.\n\"Not a too expensive one,\nChrissy. Bank roll is plndling.\u201d\nChristine arrived looking puz\nzled and found Gay at her press\ning. \u201cWell of all things! Turning\ninto regular Dot Trainer, Mrs.\nBaird.\u201d\nDot Trainer was a girl they\nknew who had married three\ny\u00a3ars before. A small income, a\nchild each year and a rigid sense\nof responsibility had forced a bent\nand blowsy middle-age upon her\nat 24. The girls often talked of\nher, holding her up as an exam\nple of what a wife should not be.\n\u201cSure. I didn\u2019t mean it. Gay.\nlove\u201d; Chris rattled on, seeing the\nsweet face bowed. \"Only I think\nyoh\u2019re carrying things too far.\nDon t let yourself go. Think he\u2019ll\nadore you if yor get yourself up\nlike a bargain basement? Don\u2019t\ngive him the notion you're a door\nmat.\u201d\n\"But when you\u2019re in love with\nsomeone like Stanley\u2014such a man\n\u2014vou don\u2019t mind sacrifices. You\nforget everything but how much\nyou want him to be happy.\u201d\n\"Well\u2014soft stuff\u2019s the begin\nning of the end. I\u2019ll tell the world.\u201d\nIn spite of herself. Gay remem\nbered Christie\u2019s warning when she\nwaited for Stanley to come home\nfrom the party.\n/Nearly all night she waited. Evi\nUAuii\nAspimn\nProved safe by millions and prescribed by physicians for\nColds Headache Neuralgia Lumbago\nPain Toothache Neuritis Rheumatism\nDOES NOT AFFECT THE HEART\n\nA Accept only \u201cBayer\u201d package\n/\"Y which contains proven directions.\nm Handy \u201cBayer\u201d boxes of 12 tablets\nV. J Also bottles of 24 and 100\u2014Druggists.\nu ta\u00ab Uada mark of Bajtr Uaoufaotora of Monomcctlcacideater of Sillcyllcacid\ndently h 6 had forgotten his deter\nmination just to \"look in.\u201d\nWhen she heard him stealing\ninto the room she turned her face\nto the wall \u2014pretended to be\nasleep.\nShe trembled as he bent over\nher; kissed her gently, turned out\nthe light. Tears ran into her eyes:\nwhen she awakened not so very\nmuch later the pillow was wet.\nBut she managed an air of\ngaiety at the breakfast table Did\nhe have a nice time? Was his\nmother pleased? Would they for\nget their anger with him\u2014be glad\nto S\u2019e him again?\n\u201cHonestly. Gay. I don\u2019t know\nwhere the time went. Was going\nDr. Reed Tells\nBy Chas.A.L.Reed,M.D.\nFormer President of the American\nMedical Association\nYOU are now in the midst of\ncold weather, when rheuma\ntism is most prevalent.\nThere are some things you ought\nto know about the cause and pre\nvention of this disease.\nRheumatism is a very vague\nterm under which are lumped to\ngether symptoms of many kinds.\nThe only common factor, and that\na doubtful one, is that they are\ncaused by a damp soil or damp\natmosphere.\nThere are two main groups of\nrheumatism, acute rheumatism, in\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES Tht National Doily MONDAY, JANUARY 17, 1927\nto stay only a minute\u2014you know?\nAnd before 1 knew it\nYes, everyone was Just as usual.\nActed as if nothing had happened.\nOh. yea\u2014mother\u2019s asked him to\ncomi for dinner soon. Perhaps he\nwould. No use hanging to a\npeeve. Reason he\u2019d stayed so late\na friend of Peg\u2019s just got back\nfrom abroad and he\u2019d been dragged\nInto a foursome. Penny was with\nPeg, of course. Girl was -Minn\nBrooks. Gay wouldn\u2019t remember\nher.\nGay did remember, though.\nTightly shingled, sleeked and\nbrushed back, bizarrely tailored\nMimi Brooks. She had a swift\nvision of her pale face laughing\nover her shoulder as she left John\nstone Baird\u2019s office with Stan\u2019s\narm around her.\nStark Fear.\nTerror coiled in her bean; shfe\nkept her eyes down so he might\nnot see the fear in them.\nShe dragged through the day\u2019s\nroutine. No snatches of song on\nher lips, no laughter in her throat.\nAsking herself questions.\nHad Stan given her a critical\nlook when he went out? Had he\nbeen in love with Mimi Brooks be\nfore he knew her\u2014Gay? Had he\nreally been dragged Into the four\nsome last night or did he want to\nbg with Mimi?\nShe brought herself up short.\n\"I\u2019m being just plain jealous. Os\ncourse, he wanted to see his\nfriends. Been shut up here with\nme for weeks and weeks. I\nhaven\u2019t any right to question.\u201d\nShe planned to make waffles\nfor dinner. A long, hard Job, but\nStan loved them and the thought\nof extra labor for him eased her\nconscience. Suspicion was a sin\nagainst love, surely.\nIn the meantime she decided to\ntake the things out of his trunk\nand pack them more carefully\nthan she had done the day be\nfore. So it happened that she\ncame across a bundle of snapshots.\nStanley his car\u2014playing tennis\n\u2014on thfe beach. Stanley alone\u2014\nin a gay crowd\u2014more often with\na girl. Always the same girl\u2014\nMinii Brooks!\nShe put the pictures together\nhastily, thrust them into a cor\nner of the trunk, jammed shut\nthe lid.\n\nJohnstone Baird\u2019s employes gave\na ball every year in April. They\nrented a ballroom at the Van Rex\neluding rheumatic fever chorea\nand rheumatic heart; and chronic\nrheumatism, which generally means\nrheumatoid arthritis or any form\nof muscular or fibrous inflamma\ntion.\nThe distinction from gout is still\nunsatisfactory, and no one is cer\ntain what causes rheumatic condi\ntions or whether all have the same\ncause.\nWhat, however. seems v sure is\nthat some of these chronic joint\ntroubles, which are often so bad\nas to cripple their victim through\nout his life, are due to infection\nby a microbe of the group called\nstreptococci.\nThese are normally present In\nthe body and play a part In' many\ninfections.\nIt is known that some cases of\nrheumatism are caused by infec\ntion from bad teeth, tonsils, sinuses\nand adenoids, and the remedy is\nobvious.\nThere remains, however, large\nnumbers of cases where the in\nfection is far more serious and\ncomes from the bowels, accord\ning to Dr. T. Izod Bennett, of\nLondon, (Journal of Royal Sani\ntary Institute. September, 1926.)\nThe popular view that rheuma\ntism is due to damp houses, damp\nclothing, bad drains,' etc.. Is\nprobably quite sound, but only be-\nI A DIVORCE\nIN PARIS\nI By Anita Loos\nTHIS is how Americans can get\ndivorced In Paris with a mini\nmum of discomfort, according to\nAnita Loos, author of \u2018\u2018Gentlemen\nPrefer Blondes,\u201d writing from the\nFrench capital for December\nHarper\u2019s Bazar: s,\n\u201cAfter a girl has her legal resi\ndence at Paris, and has her hus\nband in another legal residence,\nthe girl\u2019s lawyer is supposed to\ngo to a Parisian judge and tell\nhim that he has a married client\nwhose husband seems apposed to\nher.\n\"So then the judge says that\nhe will send one of his assistants,\nwho is called a \u2018hussier,\u2019 over to\ncall on the husband, and ask him\nIf he will not move over to his\nwife\u2019s legal residence.\n\"So this \u201chussier\u201d pays the hus\nband a call, and extends him an\ninvitation to move over to his\nwife\u2019s. And the ettiquette of it all\nIs. that the husband is supposed\nto make a stand and say, \u201cIf she\nwas the last woman on earth, I\nwould not move into her legal\nresidence.\u2019\n\u201cSo then the \u2018hussier\u2019 has got\nthe evidence lie came for, so he\ngoes away, and tells the judge\nthat he went himself with the in\nvitation but the husband declined\nit with violence So when the\ngirl appears before the'judge. the\njudge decides it\u2019s no use. and he\n\u25a0mpt* her a degree.\u201d\nFag King Discusses Some Flappers of History\nBy Fay King\nWKILAPPER\" was first used in\nEngland to denote the fledg\nlings of the family who were flap\nping around In the home nest!\nMuch as we used to say \u201ckid sis\nter.\u201d\nBut it has now become a term\napplied to any from a wise-crack\ning gold digger, to a rejuvenated\nold dame who has had her jowls\nclipped and buys her clothes in\nthe junior department to fit her\namaclated figure!\nHotel .and had a small orchestra\nand a buffet spread at midnight.\nBaird appeared briefly and made\na little speech. Afterward the\nparty was informal\u2014a sort of\nfamily affair.\nThe Coining Ball\nNow the ball was approaching;\nit was scarcely a week off.\n\u201c1 think we\u2019d better go. honey.\u2019\u2019\nStan told Gay. \"You\u2019ll enjoy get\nting out. Fun, seeing everybody\nagain.\u201d\n\u201cWell\u2014ail right, then She\nwas thinking fast, floundering a\nbit. Have to wear last year's\ndress\u2014a pretty thing, but last\nyear\u2019s. She could freshen It up\nwith a silver girdle and a rose\nAbout Prevention of Rheumatism\ncause these adverse conditions so\ndepress the system as to allow\nthe germs to take hold and mul\ntiply.\nMany persons with chronic\narthritis have been cured when\nthis particular microbe Is expel-\nTIMES DAILY\"\nFASHION\n6628. Ladies\u2019 Coat.\nCut in 6 sizes: 34, 36, 38.' 40, 42\nand 44 inches bust measure- A\n38-inch size requires 4% yards of\n40-inch material, with yard of\ncontrasting material. Price. 10c.\nBend 10c in silver or ataniint for\n\u00ab*ch \u00ab>f these iwtterns to THU\nWASHINGTON TIMES Magazine\nEditor. Print oaine and nddrcHS\nDlalnlv to Insure ororast delivery.\nSend lOe In silver or stamps for\noor UP-TO-DATE PALI. AND WIN\nTER 1926-1*37 BOOK OF FASHIONS\nState number and (ire or pattern\ndesired.\nFor two-piece sporf costumes,\nthere are a great many knitted\njumpers of two shades, white and\ngeranium, for Instance. Flemish\nblue and white or twfi tones of\ngray, ranging from pearl gray\nand slate.\nWhile the flapper considers her\nself ultra modern she is very an\ncient indeed!\nThe shrewd little flapper who\nschemes and vamps for gains and\nseeks all sorts of thrills is but a\nfeeble Imitation pf that famous\nflapper of the Nile whose petting\nparties made history. Cleopatra\nwas just 17 when she vamped\nCaesar, the greatest Roman of\nthem all. He was married, bald\nheaded and rich and powerful, and\nthe wise and wicked little Cleo\nknew how easily he would fall for\nher!\nfor the shoulder. Would there be\nmoney enough for a silver girdle?\n\u201cStanley\u2014will you be ashamed\nof me? Old clothes, you know\u2014\u201d\nHe looked at her in amaze\nment-crossed the room, snatched\nher into his arms.\n\u201cFoolish little wife! Prettiest\ngirl there, she'll be, and he that\nproud. So stveet \u2014so sweet\nHer heart rushed; she felt her\nself shining like a flame.\nDowntown Penny was turning\na rueful look upon Christine.\n\u201cDaddy Baird asked me to take\nPeg to the darned old ball. Sorry\nas the devil, Chris. What am t\nto do?\u201d\n\u201cOh\u2014all right for you, Mr,\nMan.\u201d\nled from their intestines. Its\npresence there is largely due to\noverfeeding and lack of exercise.\nIt Is not hard to see how the\nstreptococci get this hold upon\nthe bowel.\nThe growth of large towns has\nI CHILD LABOR\nINCREASES\nr[E 1927 brand of oppositiop\nto child labor legislation,\nwhether State or Federal, is to\nassert that child labor is decreas\ning\u2014In fact, that it is practical\nly non-existent. To the Fed\neral Children's Bureau of the\nUnited States Department of\nLabor, tlie country is once more\nindebted for the facts which dis\nprove this argument. The bureau\npublishes annually statistics from\nas many cities and states as can\nsupply them relative to the num\nher of children who have received\nemployment certificates\u2014in other\nwords the number of children\nwho have legally entered work\nduring the year.\nEvery year since 1922, with the\nexception of 1925, these figures\nhave increased. In 1926 the num\nber has again mounted.\nRecognizing all the factors that\nrrtight he involved\u2014an extension\nof the work certificate system to\ncover new occupations, better en\nt\u2019orcement of the \u201claw, etc-, the\nChildren\u2019s Bureau nevertheless\nconcludes that the increase is pri\nmarily the reflection u. a general\nbusiness revival which offers\ngreater opportunities of employ\ninept to children.\nThe facts are that, considering\nonly children of 14 and 15 years\nentering industry for the first\ntime, Increases were reported in\n8 Out of 12 states and in 24 out\nof 29 cities.\nThese figures collected by the\nChildren\u2019s Bureau probably repre\nsent about half the children in\nthe country receiving work per\nmits, and are typical of the coun\ntry as a whole. They giVe t o\nidea, however, of the trend if em\nployment for children entering\nsuch occupations as farm work,\ndomestic service, street trades\nand home work, for which per\nmits are not required, nor of the\nnumber of children illegally em\nployed\u2014which this same report\nindicates \"is very extensive.\nThe four cities reporting the\ngreatest increases were Fall River\nand New Bedford, Massachusetts;\nNew Britain, Connecticut; and\nYonkers, New York\u2014-all having\nan increase of over 30 per cent.\nWhite for both sport frocks and\nevening gowns Is emphasized in\nthe wardrobe of Yvonne Prin\ntemps, designed by Jeanne Lan\nvine. Gold and silver decorate\nthe evening models.\nCleo though very ancient would\nfit in nicely at any night club to\nday. She wore her hair straight\nbobbed, and glossed with oils and\npomades. She reveled In perfume,\nand much of the modern art\njewelry is copied from the rings\nand bracelets and earrings of\nher time. She wore little clothing\nand knew her onions! She was a\nfrequenter of the \u201ccabarets\u201d and\n\u201cnight\u201d clubs of that day.\nJuliet was a famous flapper of\nlater day.\nAt 16 she was desperately in\nlove with Romeo. Shakespeare\n\u201cNo, but look, Frills\u2014l wanted\nyou. Listen; can\u2019t you go vitb\nStan and Gay? I can take her\nhome early and come back for\nt you.\u201d\nShe laughed, yellow gleams in\nher eyes. \u201cNo, thanks, Lovuy-love.\nI\u2019ll manage. Save you a dance,\nthough, maybe.\u201d\nHe went back to his desk, angry.\nShe furiously called Ivor Barclay\n\u2014invited him to the ball.\nCHAPTER XXX\nIt started out joyously\u2014bright\nness, color\u2014a tide of gladness ris\ning to meet her.\nGay felt herself sparkling; felt\nherself caught in the swirl of\ngreetings, of laughter.\nled to enormous multiplication of\nmethods for preserving food for\nperiods which would have made\nit uneatable even a few years\nago. We are told to \"eat more\nfruit, but fruit is expensive and\nhardly ever fresh. Our meat, fish\nand game nearly always come\nout of cold storage, and in reach\ning the consumer are constantly\nexposed to a contaminated at\nmosphere. It is not surprising that\nhostile microbes, thus swallowed,\ncontinue to flourish inside us.\nFlush the Toxins Out!\nProper Kidney Function Is Essential to Good Health.\nSOME famous authority lias likened the feels listless, tired and achy. There are apt\nbody to a furnace. The food we eat is to be drowsy headaches and dizziness, and\nfuel that is converted into energy. The perhaps a dull, \"toxic\" backache. That the\nWaste products have been aptly termed the kidneys are not functioning as they should\n\"ashes of food.\u201d is often shown by scanty or burning secre-\nOrdinarily, our kidneys are capable of tions..\nfiltering out these waste products. But Assist your kidneys to rid the blood of\nfatigue, overwork and bad habits of diet, these with a stimulant diuretic.*\netc., often produce these body-toxins beyond Doan s Pills have won a nation-wide repu\nthe functional power of the kidneys to im- tation as a tested diuretic. They act on the\nmediately ..eliminate them. kidneys only and are endorsed from coast\nRetention of this poisonous waste within coast. Ask your neighbor!\nthe blood creates a toxic condition. One ISITS'VmZZ-twZZS\"\nDoan\u2019s Pills\nStimulant Diuretic to the Kidneys\nAt all dealers, 00c a box. Foster-Milburn Co.,Mfg. Chemists, Buffalo, N. Y.\nTeaching Worms to Turn\nWITH the aid of a T-shaped tube, electrically charged, experi\nments were conducted recently to determine whether earth\nworms possessed memory and could be taught to turn from danger.\nIt was found that they could. V\nwrote a famous tragedy founded\nupon this true story. Juliet was\nas modern as other girls in her\ntime, though It was then the\nstyle to wear long-dresses and\nlong hair.\nJoan of Arc was another fam\nous flapper. She was 17 when\nshe led the armies of France to\nvictory. She rode her horse as\ntride and wore armour. She slept\namong her soldiers on the battle\nfield.\nHistoric documents Inform us\nFloaing Into the ballroom with\nStan, so tall, so handsome, turn\ning his smile this way and that.\nAll the girls she had worked with\nadoring him as they hurried up\nto kiss her, to tumble questions\ntill she could only laugh and\nshake her head.\nShe held a little court there,\nblushing, proud\u2014all a-thrill.\nWhen the music began Stanley\nswept her out upon the floor, ex\nultantly. holding her very close,\nlaughing all the time.\n\u201cSweet thing. Did he say she\u2019d\nbe the belle? Some wife for a fel\nlow\nHer exuberance mounted. She\nhad managed the silver girdle\u2014\nMuch rheumatism is due to\nfaulty housing. The condition of\nthe house is more important than\nits site, and a well built, dry house\nin a marsh may completely pro\ntect its inhabitants from rheuma\ntism. Damp rooms, however, are\nresponsible for perhaps two-thirds\nof all the cases of rheumatism.\nEvery victim of rheumatic pains\nshould be carefully examined for\nsome focus of infection, as in\nteeth, tonsils, adenoids and intes\ntines.\nthat they thought her pretty and\nwith a good figure but that her\ngoodness and purity of thought\nand purpose was her greatest pro\ntection, and none dared harm her!\nSo you see centuries there\nwere flappers and flappers. And\ntoday a flapper can be the kind\nof a flapper she wants to be \u2014a\nhome wrecker like Cleopatra\u2014a\ngentle flapper like Juliet, or one\nwho, in spite of dress or environ\nment, can inspire the best in all\nihen, like Joan of Arc!\nmade a silver rose now caught to\nher shoulder. It was no move\npale and shining than her hair\nabove blue chiffon; ultramarine\nflounces, very simple, very young,\nthat deepened her eyes from gray\nto the color of waves when the\nwind is free.\nHer Costume\nChristine came late, startling as\na crash of cords in a smoothly\nflowing melody. She was in scar\nlet; her rouged lips red as blood\nagainst a chalky make-up. Too\nbrilliant for that company. With\nher air of casualness she became,\nin a subtle way. the personifies\ntion of all feminine lure.\n\u201cGorgeous!\" Gay whispered to\nStan. \u201cBut\u2014she\u2019s with Barclay!\nYou see? Oh\u2014here of all places!\u201d\nStanley scowled. \u201cNo sense.\nI\u2019ll speak to him later.\u201d\nGay kept smiling, smiling, but\nshe felt his anger; it threw a lit\ntle shadow on her happiness.\nChristine came to her after the\ndance was finished.\n\u2019\u2019Didn\u2019t think I\u2019d feel so con\nspicuous. I\u2019m sorry\u2014truly. Ive\nwas reasonable for once though;\nhe's gone.\u201d v\n\u201cYou\u2019ll go home with us.\nChrist?\u201d Then as her cousin\nshook her head. \u201cWhat will you\ndo?*\u2019\n\u201cYou\u2019ll see. Listen; keep an\neye on that Brooks comedy. Sta\ncia says\u2014\u201d\n(To Be Continued Tomorrow)","height":"23739","width":"18864"}}
